Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

entry.title: crudely designed mementos (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the first silver dollars of the Republic of China were crudely designed mementos (example pictured)?

entry.title: Cécile Fatiman (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Haitian Revolution began when Cécile Fatiman sacrificed a black pig, a ritual that was later repeated by Haitians resisting the United States occupation and the Duvalier dynasty?

entry.title: spearfishing event at the 2014 Micronesian Games (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a shark cost a competitor a silver medal in the spearfishing event at the 2014 Micronesian Games?

entry.title: the number 1 (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the number 1 is its own square, square root, and factorial?

entry.title: Deep Cut Gardens (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Deep Cut Gardens in New Jersey contains a stone replica of Mount Vesuvius that once erupted smoke at the behest of mobster Vito Genovese?

entry.title: the Hillbilly Thomists (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Hillbilly Thomists, a band made up of friars from the Dominican Order, reached the number-two spot on Billboard's bluegrass chart?

entry.title: Pituamkek National Park Reserve (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Pituamkek National Park Reserve, Canada's newest national park, protects a chain of barrier islands that have been used for fishing and hunting by the Mi'kmaq for 4,000 years?

entry.title: Palace Theater light bulb (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the Palace Theater light bulb has been running since 1908?

entry.title: two whales to the Great Salt Lake (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a sensational story in 1888 claimed that James Wickham, a British scientist, introduced two whales to the Great Salt Lake in an attempt to start a whale oil industry?
